Description: Handle of pottery transport amphora. Circular stamp, plain ring.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.32, 16. Possibly to be equated with one of the pieces with such a 'O' mark in the British Museum series 2011,5003.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1734)
